<th style="background-color: cornsilk">Standard drinkware</th>
<td style="background-color: cornsilk">Deep Champagne <a href="/wiki/Goblet" title="Goblet" class="mw-redirect">goblet</a></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Commonly used ingredients</th>
<td style="">
<ul>
<li>Six parts <a href="/wiki/Gordon%27s_Gin" title="Gordon's Gin">Gordon's Gin</a></li>
<li>Two parts <a href="/wiki/Vodka" title="Vodka">vodka</a></li>
<li>One part <a href="/wiki/Lillet" title="Lillet">Kina Lillet</a> (Lillet Blanc)</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="">Preparation</th>
<td style="">Shake over ice until well chilled, then strain into a deep goblet and garnish with a thin slice of lemon peel.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" style="font-size: 80%"><a href="/wiki/Cocktail_glass" title="Cocktail glass">Cocktail glasses</a> are commonly used instead of Champagne goblets in modern versions of this drink.</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>The <b>Vesper</b> or <b>Vesper <a href="/wiki/Martini_(cocktail)" title="Martini (cocktail)">Martini</a></b> is a <a href="/wiki/Cocktail" title="Cocktail">cocktail</a> that was originally made of <a href="/wiki/Gin" title="Gin">gin</a>, <a href="/wiki/Vodka" title="Vodka">vodka</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Lillet" title="Lillet">Kina Lillet</a> (in modern day named Lillet Blanc).</p>
